Titled "The Brittney Griner Story," the documentary by Alexandria Stapleton will show what Griner went through in her 10 months as a Russian prisoner, which included time in a penal colony known for its brutal conditions.

Stapleton also agrees with Griner’s point of view about the film.

"When we started, so much of BG’s story was still very foreign," Stapleton added. "And now to rewatch it and be in the midst of everything that’s exploding in Minnesota and all throughout the [United States](https://www.foxnews.com/category/us), it’s crazy. I hope people can watch this story and see it as a cautionary tale … almost knock some sense into people.

